A group under the aegis of Barutem Patriotic Agenda (BPA) have sympathized with the Kwara State governor, Abdulrahman Abdulrazaq over the demise of his father, Alh. Abdulganiyu Folorunsho Abdul-Razaq, SAN (OFR), who passed away in his sleep in the early hours of Saturday morning. The group described the death of the late Mutawali of Ilorin and Tafida of Zazzau as a loss to the entire northern Nigeria even as it prayed for the eternal repose of his soul. A release signed by the group’s president, Adam Sidi Oumar said: “The entire members of Barutem Patriotic Agenda (BPA) wish to express our deepest sympathies to the entire AbdulRazaq family. May God give you the comfort and peace that you seek and may the soul of Baba, Lawyer AbdulGaniyu Folorunsho AbdulRazaq (SAN) rest in Aljanatil Firdaus. “No doubt, the entire Northern Nigeria has lost one of it’s prides. “We pray Allah also grants the entire country, Northern Nigeria and Kwarans the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss.”